						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the Ayyaṉār temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman (Rājarāja I): Year 9 = 993-94 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is fragmentary.</p>						

						<p>It mentions a certain <hi rend="italic">maṉṟāḍi</hi> Maḻapāḍi Śoguḍaṉ, son of Vaḍugaṉ Maḻapāḍi, residing at Śiṟumaruvūr a <hi rend="italic">piḍāgai</hi> (hamlet) of Śrīgaṇḍarādittachaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">Brahmadēyam</hi> on the northern bank <hi rend="italic">(vaḍakarai)</hi> (of the Kāvērī).</p>						

